The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                 LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 ING Vysya has launched a unit-linked savings plan  ING Prime Life  that offers returns up to 200 per cent on fund allocation charges. For a 15-year policy term, 125 per cent of the initial allocation charges are returned, whereas for a 20-year term, 200 per cent of the fund allocation is returned. The plan offers 5 per cent increase on the base sum assured every year. ING Life Insurance has a paid-up capital of Rs 1,019.2 crore. It is present in 234 cities and has 367 sales teams.                             
	 Taurus Mutual Fund has announced the launch of Taurus Ethical Fund. The new fund offer for the open-ended diversified equity fund opened on February 19 and will close on March 30. The fund will invest only in Indian companies that are listed and Shariah-compliant, which means adherence to fundamental Islamic principles.                             
	 Max New York Life Insurance has introduced electronic fund transfer for settling policyholders claims. The system will ensure a smooth settlement of approved claims within 72 hours of submitting the documents. The amount due under the settlement will be credited directly to the claimants bank account.                                                                                                                                
